February 13, 2019
U.S.-Colombia Relations
2019-02-13T23:50:58-05:00https://images.c-span.org/Files/f55/20190213123159013_hd.jpgPresident Trump and first lady Melania Trump met with President Iván Duque Márquez of Colombia and first lady Maria Juliana Ruiz in the Oval Office. The two leaders discussed U.S.-Colombia relations as well as the political situation in Venezuela. President Trump was also asked whether he would sign a potential border security deal struck by congressional negotiators. “We haven’t gotten it yet. We’ll be getting it. We’ll be looking for landmines,” he said. “I don’t want to see a shutdown. Shutdown would be a terrible thing.”
President Trump and first lady Melania Trump met with President Iván Duque Márquez of Colombia and first lady Maria Juliana Ruiz in the Oval Office. The two leaders discussed… read more
President Trump and first lady Melania Trump met with President Iván Duque Márquez of Colombia and first lady Maria Juliana Ruiz in the Oval Office. The two leaders discussed U.S.-Colombia relations as well as the political situation in Venezuela. President Trump was also asked whether he would sign a potential border security deal struck by congressional negotiators. “We haven’t gotten it yet. We’ll be getting it. We’ll be looking for landmines,” he said. “I don’t want to see a shutdown. Shutdown would be a terrible thing.” close
